	How do I help MarilynJean grow?</p>
<p>
	Kids? Yep. Shoes? Yep. Apparel, Toys and Active Wear? Yep. And maybe even a few more we haven&#39;t thought of yet.</p>
<p>
	This is an &#39;All Call&#39; for smart, savvy, style-obsessed Buyers who want to be part of something fun and innovative and who want to make a real impact on the company they work for.</p>
<p>
	MarilynJean buyers are responsible for sourcing compelling product assortments, negotiating and developing vendor partnerships, and delivering great brands at amazing products to our Moms, Babies &amp; Kids!</p>
<p>
	HOW WILL I IMPACT THE BUSINESS?<br />
	<br />
	By finding and acquiring a compelling product assortment and a great price that make our Moms, Babies &amp; kids happily shop!<br />
	<br />
	We set our self apart with our amazing team and experienced merchants who have an obsession with style and an unmatched loyalty and commitment to making our company the best online experience for our members. If you are a proven self-starter who can problem solve on-the-fly, loves the kids industry and has an analytic mind managing your revenues - then talk to us!<br />
	<br />
	Responsibilities include:</p>
<p>
	&bull; Identify brands and product that represent our customer&rsquo;s demand!<br />
	&bull; Represent and share the details and successes of our company with potential partners.<br />
	&bull; Negotiate, build and source compelling product assortments at discounted prices.<br />
	&bull; Drive sales through the selection of product, pricing, promotion for greatest return on investment.<br />
	&bull; Buying responsibility and financial accountability for respective buying category<br />
	&bull; Negotiate buying terms with vendors (price, quantity, delivery/ payment terms)<br />
	&bull; Manage the three day event operations with an Assistant Buyer<br />
	&bull; Build strong relationships with vendors<br />
	Qualifications should include:</p>
<p>
	&bull; 3+ years&rsquo; buying experience, preferably with branded merchandise. Categories include apparel for babies, boys, girls, tween, women&#39;s, footwear, tween, and various hard goods (toys, games, books, furniture, etc).<br />
	&bull; Strong understanding of merchandising financials and the ability to manage profitability<br />
	&bull; Knowledge of Open-to Buy process<br />
	&bull; Experience in internet merchandising<br />
	&bull; Discount/ liquidation retail experience a plus<br />
	&bull; Experience &amp; Passion for the kids&#39; industry would be great!</p>
